JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in the North West has instructed its MPs to vote in favour of President Jacob Zuma next week. Opposition parties have tabled a motion of no confidence in the president.It will be heard on 18 April.READ: ANC MPs stand by Zuma: MthembuThe party says MPs must respect the ANC and remain loyal when making their mark in Parliament.It says calls for Zuma's removal come from rich imperialists, who want to remove the ANC from power.The provincial branch has welcomed Zuma's unpopular cabinet shake-up and reaffirms its confidence in the his leadership.eNCA